because the Fed can impact the overall market.

42
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:29,239
Never forget three out of four stocks

43
00:01:29,239 --> 00:01:30,480
follow the overall market.

44
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,439
So I'm using lots of different technology,

45
00:01:32,439 --> 00:01:33,879
lots of different sources,

46
00:01:33,879 --> 00:01:36,079
and I'm trying to get a better grasp

47
00:01:36,079 --> 00:01:37,799
of what's going on in the market.

48
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:40,379
Obviously, I've been trading 25 years now,

49
00:01:40,379 --> 00:01:41,799
teaching for 15 years.

50
00:01:41,799 --> 00:01:43,239
The markets have changed a lot

51
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:45,000
and they're gonna continue to change,

52
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,799
but understand several lessons later on in this video,

53
00:01:47,799 --> 00:01:50,000
they're gonna help you trade in today's world.

54
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,640
It's very important to always be adapting to the market.

55
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,400
You don't wanna just sit on lessons

56
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,840
that you learned a decade ago

57
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,280
and then they don't really apply here.

58
00:01:57,280 --> 00:02:01,420
So all of these lessons are made for you in today's world.

59
00:02:01,420 --> 00:02:04,340
Lesson number two, great success takes time.

60
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:05,640
Rome wasn't built in a day.

61
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,939
Don't roll your eyes, okay?

62
00:02:06,939 --> 00:02:08,120
You need to hear this.

63
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:10,080
It is a marathon and not a sprint.

64
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:12,919
My own millions and my now 50 millionaire students,

65
00:02:12,919 --> 00:02:14,539
they took years to achieve.

66
00:02:14,539 --> 00:02:17,000
I wish someone had told me these lessons in the beginning.

67
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,520
This is why I got started of being a teacher.

68
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,560
For example, when I was running my hedge fund,

69
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,900
I met with this one investor

70
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:24,780
who didn't end up investing with me,

71
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:26,979
but he shared a very valuable lesson with me

72
00:02:26,979 --> 00:02:29,819
and he made me feel like crap in the moment

73
00:02:29,819 --> 00:02:31,780
where he said, I'm not gonna invest in your fund.

74
00:02:31,780 --> 00:02:32,900
You're not scarred.

75
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,900
And I was like, what are you talking about old man?

76
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:36,419
I have this great track record.

77
00:02:36,419 --> 00:02:37,419
I've made so much money.

78
00:02:37,419 --> 00:02:39,340
And this was the only one I made like 2 million

79
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:40,699
at the time I was very cocky.

80
00:02:40,699 --> 00:02:42,099
I didn't have the proper perspective.

81
00:02:42,099 --> 00:02:43,580
And he said, I love your strategy.

82
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:46,020
I love your passion, but you're not scarred yet.

83
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:48,139
In the moment, I was like, what are you talking about?

84
00:02:48,139 --> 00:02:51,620
After I lost a million dollars on Cygnus E transactions

85
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:53,900
and I had a really nasty scar from that,

86
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:55,979
although it taught me to cut losses quickly,

87
00:02:55,979 --> 00:02:58,580
I then understood why he wouldn't invest in me

88
00:02:58,580 --> 00:03:01,379
because I hadn't developed risk management yet.

89
00:03:01,379 --> 00:03:02,580
I wasn't scarred.

90
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:04,740
So even though I knew how to profit,

91
00:03:04,740 --> 00:03:07,000
I didn't know how to lose properly.

92
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,539
And that was just one example,

93
00:03:08,539 --> 00:03:11,419
but I did not know where I was in my journey

94
00:03:11,419 --> 00:03:14,419
because that man, and I think he was like in his 60s

95
00:03:14,419 --> 00:03:16,580
or 70s, he had a lot more experience

96
00:03:16,580 --> 00:03:19,020
and he knew exactly where I was in my journey.

97
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:22,900
So for me, I now recognize the importance of his advice.

98
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:24,259
Back then, I had no idea.

99
00:03:24,259 --> 00:03:25,620
I thought he was just a crazy old man.

100
00:03:25,620 --> 00:03:29,340
Lesson number three, focus on trading small at first

101
00:03:29,340 --> 00:03:31,219
and survive your learning curve.

102
00:03:31,219 --> 00:03:33,460
Myself, I made too much money in the beginning,

103
00:03:33,460 --> 00:03:34,280
but I was lucky.

104
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,120
I'm like Forrest Gump.

105
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,099
I got started right away.

106
00:03:36,099 --> 00:03:37,979
There was a mania and I made a million dollars.

107
00:03:37,979 --> 00:03:41,060
That actually held me back my entire trading career

108
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:43,159
because I had too much success in the beginning.

109
00:03:43,159 --> 00:03:45,560
If you now look at my 50 millionaire students,

110
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:48,000
none of them have too much success in the beginning.

111
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,840
Why?

112
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,400
Because they're so focused on studying, trading small,

113
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,039
building the proper foundation.

114
00:03:53,039 --> 00:03:56,699
Your initial profit and loss is irrelevant in the long run.

115
00:03:56,699 --> 00:03:58,400
In fact, it's actually counterintuitive.

116
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,240
If you make too much money too quickly

117
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,080
and you get too cocky,

118
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,919
it holds you back like it did for me,

119
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:05,000
but you need that foundation of knowledge

120
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,800
like how to pick the right stocks,

121
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,599
what are the best setups to look for,

122
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:12,280
and most importantly, knowing how to minimize losses

123
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,620
and how to cut losses.

124
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:15,639
You don't need to let a small mistake

125
00:04:15,639 --> 00:04:17,759
turn into a potential disaster.

126
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:19,160
That can really hold you back

127
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,399
because I know a lot of traders,

128
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:24,399
they lose 20, 30, 40, 50, 70% of their account.

129
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:26,560
And even though they might be able to make it back,

130
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,040
it holds them back for a while.

131
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,639
Mentally, they're in pain.

132
00:04:29,639 --> 00:04:32,079
Mentally, they're screwed up.

133
00:04:32,079 --> 00:04:34,139
You don't wanna take those big losses.

134
00:04:34,139 --> 00:04:37,639
It's very difficult to get back on your momentum track.

135
00:04:37,639 --> 00:04:41,000
So I have lots of one, two, 3% losses these days.

136
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,360
A lot of my top students do.

137
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,399
You might be surprised,

138
00:04:43,399 --> 00:04:46,279
but a lot of my top students are only winning 40, 50,

139
00:04:46,279 --> 00:04:47,720
55% of the time.

140
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:51,139
Not 70, 80, 90% of the time, like most people think.

141
00:04:51,139 --> 00:04:51,980
Why?

142
00:04:51,980 --> 00:04:53,680
Because they're wrong a lot while they're testing,

143
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:56,759
but their losses are much smaller compared to their gains

144
00:04:56,759 --> 00:04:58,120
so their account rises.

145
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:00,079
I'll talk more about that in a future lesson,

146
00:05:00,079 --> 00:05:01,100
but understand right now,

147
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,399
I'm refocusing the content on my channel

148
00:05:03,399 --> 00:05:06,199
to cover this more foundational day trading knowledge

149
00:05:06,199 --> 00:05:07,279
that is relevant today

150
00:05:07,279 --> 00:05:09,800
because I know you don't think that the foundation matters.

151
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:10,639
It does.

152
00:05:10,639 --> 00:05:12,740
All great traders started somewhere.

153
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:15,480
For example, if you only have $1,000 to trade,

154
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:18,000
definitely watch my video on how to start trading

155
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,759
with only $1,000 and exactly what I would do

156
00:05:20,759 --> 00:05:24,199
and my video on how to trade stocks with zero experience.

157
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:25,600
You need this foundation.

158
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,360
It's good to review the basics.

159
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,600
Getting back to the lessons, lesson number four,

160
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:32,800
I really want you to focus on lesser known niches, okay?

161
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,160
Especially when starting out,

162
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:37,800
focusing on smaller niches like micro caps and small caps,

163
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,379
there might be less money overall to make.

164
00:05:40,379 --> 00:05:43,000
Everyone wants to trade Tesla and Amazon,

165
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,560
the biggest companies and Forex,

166
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:47,160
but you have more edge and opportunity

167
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:49,319
to excel in these small niches.

168
00:05:49,319 --> 00:05:52,959
It's very hard to be big traders at their big games.

169
00:05:52,959 --> 00:05:54,480
I wouldn't trade Forex at all.

170
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,680
You actually have no edge whatsoever.

171
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,360
And yet Forex, why?

172
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,920
Because it's the most liquid,

173
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:02,680
the most popular trading industry in the world.

174
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,439
So you're competing against billionaires.

175
00:06:04,439 --> 00:06:05,279
Guess what?

176
00:06:05,279 --> 00:06:06,120
If you're playing basketball,

177
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:08,680
you don't want to play against Michael Jordan

178
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,759
or Kobe Bryant or LeBron James.

179
00:06:10,759 --> 00:06:13,519
You want to take on players that you can win against.

180
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:15,920
I don't want to be in the same niche as billionaires

181
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,720
because I have no chance at winning.

182
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:20,079
They have so much more experience, so much more capital,

183
00:06:20,079 --> 00:06:22,199
so many more technologies.

184
00:06:22,199 --> 00:06:23,680
Average people don't have a chance.

185
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,480
With small caps and micro caps,

186
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,240
my 50 millionaire students prove,

187
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,519
none of us are that smart,

188
00:06:28,519 --> 00:06:30,100
none of us are that great at math,

189
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:32,040
but because it's such a smaller niche,

190
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:35,399
the smartest, most well-prepared traders,

191
00:06:35,399 --> 00:06:37,220
the biggest traders, the biggest investors,

192
00:06:37,220 --> 00:06:39,879
they don't care about this quote, small time stuff.

193
00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:41,959
Even Jack Kellogg, my millionaire trader,

194
00:06:41,959 --> 00:06:44,120
a student with $20 million now,

195
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,600
he laughs at some of the setups that I trade.

196
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,360
He's like, why would I trade that setup?

197
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:50,120
You can only make a few thousand dollars

198
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,720
because now he's so rich.

199
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:54,079
So I want you to focus on these plays

200
00:06:54,079 --> 00:06:56,839
where you can quote, only make a few thousand dollars.

201
00:06:56,839 --> 00:06:59,240
That's where the edge is, that's where it's easier.

202
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:02,300
To give a business example, eBay was started

203
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:05,019
when the founder just wanted to sell Pez dispensers

204
00:07:05,019 --> 00:07:07,519
and eBay turned into a multi-billion dollar business

205
00:07:07,519 --> 00:07:09,040
starting with Pez dispensers.

206
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,860
You don't have to go for home runs.

207
00:07:10,860 --> 00:07:12,339
You don't have to try to make billions.

208
00:07:12,339 --> 00:07:15,079
Start small, focus on niches, and you'll succeed.

209
00:07:15,079 --> 00:07:17,100
Don't worry, I know you're worried right now,

210
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,139
but I'm gonna share all my favorite niches

211
00:07:19,139 --> 00:07:20,259
in a future video.

212
00:07:20,259 --> 00:07:24,209
So be sure to like, comment, and subscribe.

213
00:07:24,209 --> 00:07:27,410
Lesson number five, you'll never be right 100% of the time.

214
00:07:27,410 --> 00:07:29,529
You have to learn to control your losses

215
00:07:29,529 --> 00:07:31,009
when you are wrong, okay?

216
00:07:31,009 --> 00:07:34,569
Any one loss doesn't really matter if you control it.

217
00:07:34,569 --> 00:07:35,889
If you lose, lose, lose,

218
00:07:35,889 --> 00:07:39,290
but you're losing 1%, 2%, 3%, those losses are fine.

219
00:07:39,290 --> 00:07:40,689
They're basically scratches.

220
00:07:40,689 --> 00:07:42,449
On your wins, if you have a single,

221
00:07:42,449 --> 00:07:45,990
which I consider like a five or 10% or a 15 or 20%,

222
00:07:45,990 --> 00:07:48,089
whether it's my student, whether it's myself,

223
00:07:48,089 --> 00:07:50,370
the whole key is growing your accounts.

224
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:53,670
Personally, I have a lot of one, two, 3% losses.

225
00:07:53,670 --> 00:07:54,670
I'm fine with that.

226
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:56,009
I've become fine with that.

227
00:07:56,009 --> 00:07:58,569
In the past, when I was worried about being perfect,

228
00:07:58,569 --> 00:08:00,209
like when that old man told me

229
00:08:00,209 --> 00:08:01,689
that I hadn't been scarred yet,

230
00:08:01,689 --> 00:08:03,649
some of my losses were huge

231
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:05,889
because I didn't wanna take a small loss.

232
00:08:05,889 --> 00:08:08,870
Now I'm completely open to taking a small loss.

233
00:08:08,870 --> 00:08:11,149
The key is keeping your discipline

234
00:08:11,149 --> 00:08:13,430
and your winners being bigger than your losses.

235
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:17,430
So any one loss doesn't kill your account or your momentum

236
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:18,949
and your account grows over time.

237
00:08:18,949 --> 00:08:21,870
And understand, just because you lose monetarily

238
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:23,949
doesn't mean that it's a complete waste.

239
00:08:23,949 --> 00:08:26,629
In fact, you actually learn more from your losses.

240
00:08:26,629 --> 00:08:29,430
When I am wrong and I lose 1%, 2%, 3%,

241
00:08:29,430 --> 00:08:31,589
I just won't trade that setup again.

242
00:08:31,589 --> 00:08:33,769
That's how you learn what not to do.

243
00:08:33,769 --> 00:08:36,230
Your losses actually are your best teachers.

244
00:08:36,230 --> 00:08:39,789
Lesson number six, do not short sell, okay?

245
00:08:39,789 --> 00:08:42,149
I used to make millions of dollars short selling

246
00:08:42,149 --> 00:08:43,490
but times have changed.

247
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:45,190
And now there's so many short sellers,

248
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:47,309
the squeezes have become so crazy.

249
00:08:47,309 --> 00:08:50,509
Even pros risk losing six and seven figures

250
00:08:50,509 --> 00:08:51,649
on some of these squeezes.

251
00:08:51,649 --> 00:08:53,190
Even if the company is a scam,

252
00:08:53,190 --> 00:08:54,789
even if it's a junk company,

253
00:08:54,789 --> 00:08:56,850
even if the stock eventually crashes,

254
00:08:56,850 --> 00:08:58,990
newbies have almost no chance

255
00:08:58,990 --> 00:09:00,490
at winning short selling right now.

256
00:09:00,490 --> 00:09:02,250
This is a lesson that I've learned

257
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:04,149
and I know it's tough and some people say,

258
00:09:04,230 --> 00:09:06,590
oh Tim, you're a trader, you used to short sell,

259
00:09:06,590 --> 00:09:08,149
you taught everyone how to short sell.

260
00:09:08,149 --> 00:09:11,590
Yes, but again, I am a trader, not a traitor.

261
00:09:11,590 --> 00:09:13,549
There's a difference of spelling there

262
00:09:13,549 --> 00:09:14,669
and it's very important.

263
00:09:14,669 --> 00:09:17,149
Traders with a D, adapt.

264
00:09:17,149 --> 00:09:19,590
Traitors, well, they're just evil, okay?

265
00:09:19,590 --> 00:09:24,029
Benedict Arnold included, but I trade and I adapt.

266
00:09:24,029 --> 00:09:25,529
So short selling, yes,

267
00:09:25,529 --> 00:09:27,590
maybe if you have enough experience, enough money,

268
00:09:27,590 --> 00:09:29,850
you can overcome some of these short squeezes.

269
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:32,710
But lately we're seeing stocks spike from three,

270
00:09:32,710 --> 00:09:35,230
not just from three to 10 when I used to short sell.

271
00:09:35,230 --> 00:09:37,710
Now some of these stocks are spiking three to 20,

272
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:41,669
three to 50, three to a hundred in a few hours, okay?

273
00:09:41,669 --> 00:09:43,470
And understand as you're short selling,

274
00:09:43,470 --> 00:09:45,590
you can lose much more than you put in.

275
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:47,590
So you don't just lose all your money,

276
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:49,389
you can lose multiples of your money.

277
00:09:49,389 --> 00:09:51,470
And then the money doesn't just disappear,

278
00:09:51,470 --> 00:09:54,309
the broker will actually report you to the credit agencies.

279
00:09:54,309 --> 00:09:56,590
Some traders actually declare bankruptcy

280
00:09:56,590 --> 00:09:58,850
so they don't have to pay their debts from short selling.

281
00:09:58,850 --> 00:10:01,190
It is a very, very slippery slope

282
00:10:01,190 --> 00:10:02,669
and it's partially my fault

283
00:10:02,669 --> 00:10:04,870
because I've popularized short selling

284
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:06,269
small caps and micro caps.

285
00:10:06,269 --> 00:10:07,110
But guess what?

286
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:07,950
You can adapt.

287
00:10:07,950 --> 00:10:09,309
And the beautiful thing is

288
00:10:09,309 --> 00:10:12,789
because short selling has become so scary for short sellers,

289
00:10:12,789 --> 00:10:15,629
it's become an absolute blessing for longs.

290
00:10:15,629 --> 00:10:18,629
Imagine writing a stock that goes from three to 60

291
00:10:18,629 --> 00:10:20,909
or five to a hundred in a few hours.

292
00:10:20,909 --> 00:10:22,950
You can grow your account very fast

293
00:10:22,950 --> 00:10:24,470
by focusing on the long side.

294
00:10:24,470 --> 00:10:26,070
This is what trading is all about.

295
00:10:26,070 --> 00:10:27,929
Weeding out patterns that don't work

296
00:10:27,929 --> 00:10:29,710
or are too risky or stressful

297
00:10:29,710 --> 00:10:31,230
and partaking in patterns

298
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:33,470
where there's a ton of opportunity and upside.

299
00:10:33,470 --> 00:10:35,470
So this brings me to lesson number seven.

300
00:10:35,470 --> 00:10:39,509
Do not be afraid to bet bigger on perfect setups, okay?

301
00:10:39,509 --> 00:10:41,710
Small companies, new technologies,

302
00:10:41,710 --> 00:10:44,549
they can go supernova faster than ever before.

303
00:10:44,549 --> 00:10:47,350
Stocks don't just double or triple in a few days

304
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:49,149
or a few weeks in this market.

305
00:10:49,149 --> 00:10:52,190
They can go up 10, 20, a hundred times

306
00:10:52,190 --> 00:10:54,070
in a few hours or in a few days.

307
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:57,149
So be open-minded and be willing to dream big

308
00:10:57,149 --> 00:10:58,269
and take action.

309
00:10:58,269 --> 00:11:00,750
But only if you've studied the setups,

310
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:02,629
only if you're fully prepared.

311
00:11:02,629 --> 00:11:05,669
It's very scary when these stocks go up and down so fast.

312
00:11:05,669 --> 00:11:07,710
I don't want you to think that every stock

313
00:11:07,710 --> 00:11:09,509
is gonna go supernova and keep going up

314
00:11:09,509 --> 00:11:12,990
because the market is very unforgiving on the way down.

315
00:11:12,990 --> 00:11:16,710
This is the business we've chosen.

316
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:19,190
So I want you to take profits along the way.

317
00:11:19,190 --> 00:11:20,470
Just in the past few weeks,

318
00:11:20,470 --> 00:11:23,750
we've seen several supernovas that have gone up five, 10,

319
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:25,750
20 times in a few hours.

320
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:30,350
We saw CWD, we saw OCTO, we saw QMMM.

321
00:11:30,350 --> 00:11:34,269
Just the other day, WLDS went from two to 10 in 10 minutes.

322
00:11:34,269 --> 00:11:36,470
I literally was on the phone with my programmer

323
00:11:36,470 --> 00:11:38,669
where having a technical issue with the website.

324
00:11:38,669 --> 00:11:40,470
And while I was on the phone with him,

325
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:41,789
trying to get a video lesson up,

326
00:11:41,789 --> 00:11:44,590
the stock went from two to 10, literally in 10 minutes.

327
00:11:44,590 --> 00:11:45,429
And I missed it.

328
00:11:45,429 --> 00:11:47,830
Later on in this video, I'm gonna share my lessons

329
00:11:47,830 --> 00:11:50,669
of how to cut losses and how to take profits properly.

330
00:11:50,669 --> 00:11:51,509
So stay tuned.

331
00:11:51,509 --> 00:11:53,509
I'm also sharing my favorite trade setups

332
00:11:53,509 --> 00:11:55,190
in one of my next videos.

333
00:11:55,190 --> 00:11:56,809
All of the videos I'm mentioning

334
00:11:56,809 --> 00:11:58,370
will be linked in the description.

335
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:00,049
So feel free to click around.

336
00:12:00,049 --> 00:12:01,110
It's all about learning.

337
00:12:01,110 --> 00:12:03,929
And if any video that I mentioned is not published yet,

338
00:12:03,929 --> 00:12:05,889
subscribe to the channel so you don't miss it.

339
00:12:05,889 --> 00:12:07,909
We're gonna keep creating more and more videos.

340
00:12:07,909 --> 00:12:10,330
Shout out to Carrie, who's helping organize everything.

341
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:12,549
Lesson number eight, know who to learn from

342
00:12:12,549 --> 00:12:14,049
and who you shouldn't learn from.

343
00:12:14,049 --> 00:12:16,629
This is very important and I learned this the hard way.

344
00:12:16,629 --> 00:12:19,090
Sadly, most people in this industry are fake

345
00:12:19,090 --> 00:12:20,870
or they're just mediocre performers.

346
00:12:20,870 --> 00:12:22,950
They're not gonna really help you achieve much.

347
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:25,230
So surround yourself with proven winners

348
00:12:25,230 --> 00:12:27,830
like my 50 top students and myself.

349
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:29,429
My team and I worked very hard.

350
00:12:29,429 --> 00:12:31,230
For example, in the beginning,

351
00:12:31,230 --> 00:12:33,470
when I wasn't teaching just when I was trading,

352
00:12:33,470 --> 00:12:36,190
I was on a bunch of different websites and chat rooms.

353
00:12:36,190 --> 00:12:38,950
A lot of traders would share their entry price.

354
00:12:38,950 --> 00:12:40,769
They would say, oh, this stock looks amazing.

355
00:12:40,769 --> 00:12:41,669
I'm gonna buy this.

356
00:12:41,669 --> 00:12:43,529
And everyone in the chat room or the website

357
00:12:43,529 --> 00:12:44,710
would get very excited.

358
00:12:44,710 --> 00:12:46,710
The stock would go up as everyone bought.

359
00:12:46,710 --> 00:12:49,169
And then for some reason, the chat leader,

360
00:12:49,169 --> 00:12:52,070
the website leader would never say when they were selling.

361
00:12:52,070 --> 00:12:52,909
Why?

362
00:12:52,909 --> 00:12:54,149
Because they were pumping up the stock.

363
00:12:54,149 --> 00:12:57,509
They didn't care when other people were in the stock

364
00:12:57,509 --> 00:12:59,169
or when it was the best time to sell.

365
00:12:59,169 --> 00:13:01,570
They specifically just wanted to pump up the stock.

366
00:13:01,570 --> 00:13:03,750
And there's a lot of websites and chat rooms like this

367
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:04,950
where it's follow the leader.

368
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:07,750
I encourage you to never follow anybody's alerts.

369
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:10,730
I only share my alerts so that you can learn my process

370
00:13:10,730 --> 00:13:11,750
and my mindset.

371
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,590
It's all about becoming self-sufficient.

372
00:13:13,590 --> 00:13:15,750
I talk a lot about my 50 millionaire students.

373
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:16,990
Yes, they made a lot of money,

374
00:13:16,990 --> 00:13:19,309
but they know their patterns inside and out.

375
00:13:19,309 --> 00:13:20,909
They trade their own process.

376
00:13:20,909 --> 00:13:22,269
They don't need anybody else.

377
00:13:22,269 --> 00:13:24,269
And that I think is the best way to learn

378
00:13:24,269 --> 00:13:26,070
so that you're self-sufficient too.

379
00:13:26,070 --> 00:13:28,950
So be careful, especially when you have a lot of traders

380
00:13:28,950 --> 00:13:30,669
where they're not sharing their losses,

381
00:13:30,669 --> 00:13:32,070
they're not sharing their exits.

382
00:13:32,070 --> 00:13:34,190
They don't really care about anybody else.

383
00:13:34,190 --> 00:13:35,149
That's very dangerous.

384
00:13:35,149 --> 00:13:37,149
So if you wanna learn more from me,

385
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,370
definitely sign up for my newsletter below.

386
00:13:39,370 --> 00:13:41,710
I promise to teach you everything I know

387
00:13:41,710 --> 00:13:43,830
and it's only gonna be good for you, so use it.

388
00:13:43,830 --> 00:13:47,509
Lesson number nine, your mindset dictates your success.

389
00:13:47,509 --> 00:13:49,190
You have to believe in yourself.

390
00:13:49,190 --> 00:13:52,830
You have to stay dedicated, patient, and positive, okay?

391
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:54,789
There is no time for negativity

392
00:13:54,789 --> 00:13:57,830
and you shouldn't also expect overnight success,

393
00:13:57,830 --> 00:13:59,990
but there's a lot of negative people in your life,

394
00:13:59,990 --> 00:14:01,389
probably on social media.

395
00:14:01,389 --> 00:14:03,029
You have to tune them out.

396
00:14:03,029 --> 00:14:06,250
I know that they'll say that you can achieve amazing success.

397
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:08,350
They're right, you can achieve overnight success,

398
00:14:08,350 --> 00:14:10,690
but you can achieve anything in the long run.

399
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:11,529
I've learned that.

400
00:14:11,529 --> 00:14:13,149
50 of my millionaire students have learned that.

401
00:14:13,149 --> 00:14:17,710
So do not be in a rush for millions of dollars overnight.

402
00:14:17,710 --> 00:14:19,029
I just wanna be clear about that.

403
00:14:19,029 --> 00:14:20,429
You're gonna make bad decisions.

404
00:14:20,429 --> 00:14:22,190
A lot of people think that they can do

405
00:14:22,190 --> 00:14:24,389
all of these amazing things overnight

406
00:14:24,389 --> 00:14:25,629
and they want their leverage,

407
00:14:25,629 --> 00:14:29,230
they wanna just get the immediate payoff, don't, okay?

408
00:14:29,230 --> 00:14:31,190
Have perspective, be patient.

409
00:14:31,190 --> 00:14:34,090
The best rewards, the biggest rewards happen over time.

410
00:14:34,090 --> 00:14:36,070
Remember, this is not just about money.

411
00:14:36,070 --> 00:14:38,110
This is about your knowledge and experience

412
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:40,269
and later that translates into money.

413
00:14:40,269 --> 00:14:42,850
So this is a very difficult lesson for myself

414
00:14:42,850 --> 00:14:44,830
because I'm a very impatient person,

415
00:14:44,830 --> 00:14:48,870
but once I took away these time limits that were self-imposed,

416
00:14:48,870 --> 00:14:51,149
I was actually a much more successful trader

417
00:14:51,149 --> 00:14:52,789
and a much more successful teacher.

418
00:14:52,789 --> 00:14:55,830
Time is actually on your side if you stay dedicated.

419
00:14:55,830 --> 00:14:59,590
Lesson number 10, seasonality and history matter, okay?

420
00:14:59,590 --> 00:15:01,230
It doesn't matter how prepared you are.

421
00:15:01,230 --> 00:15:02,850
You might have studied everything

422
00:15:02,850 --> 00:15:04,629
and you're like, okay, now's the time.

423
00:15:04,629 --> 00:15:08,029
But if you're in a bear market or if the market crashes

424
00:15:08,029 --> 00:15:09,309
or maybe it's a slow season,

425
00:15:09,309 --> 00:15:10,909
it doesn't matter how much you study.

426
00:15:10,909 --> 00:15:12,789
There's not gonna be that many opportunities.

427
00:15:12,789 --> 00:15:15,110
There's not gonna be that much money to be made.

428
00:15:15,110 --> 00:15:18,750
So understand that the market goes through different cycles.

429
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:21,909
Let me tell you why I go to Italy every summer.

430
00:15:21,909 --> 00:15:25,110
I'm very blessed to have a beautiful villa in Italy

431
00:15:25,110 --> 00:15:27,190
that I go to every single summer.

432
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:30,149
But why do I go there specifically every summer?

433
00:15:30,149 --> 00:15:32,070
Because the summer is slower,

434
00:15:32,070 --> 00:15:33,610
specifically July and August.

435
00:15:33,610 --> 00:15:36,269
Those are historically the two slowest months of the year,

436
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:38,110
although lately in this bull market,

437
00:15:38,110 --> 00:15:39,190
it hasn't even been slow.

438
00:15:39,190 --> 00:15:41,350
But usually those two months are slower

439
00:15:41,350 --> 00:15:44,149
and you'll find that a lot of the most successful traders,

440
00:15:44,149 --> 00:15:45,750
the most successful investors in the world,

441
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:46,889
they take some time off.

442
00:15:46,889 --> 00:15:48,970
This is not a normal nine to five job.

443
00:15:48,970 --> 00:15:50,090
You can take time off.

444
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:52,409
It's good for your mental stability.

445
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:54,929
It's fun, it's good to bring your friends and your family.

446
00:15:54,929 --> 00:15:57,929
But at the same time, recognize when the times are slower.

447
00:15:57,929 --> 00:15:59,269
And I actually have a great story

448
00:15:59,269 --> 00:16:02,110
from one of the traders who were out there this past summer.

449
00:16:02,110 --> 00:16:02,950
His name is Joe.

450
00:16:02,950 --> 00:16:04,289
He's made millions of dollars

451
00:16:04,289 --> 00:16:06,610
and he was just chilling, drinking.

452
00:16:06,610 --> 00:16:08,929
And I was like, Joe, Joe, the market's on fire.

453
00:16:08,929 --> 00:16:09,970
And I was still trading

454
00:16:09,970 --> 00:16:12,850
because I'm sometimes a degenerate gambler myself.

455
00:16:12,850 --> 00:16:13,850
I try to teach you,

456
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:15,809
but I also have lessons to learn myself.

457
00:16:15,809 --> 00:16:17,570
And Joe said, looked at me and he's like,

458
00:16:17,570 --> 00:16:18,450
what are you doing?

459
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:19,649
I was like, there's so many plays.

460
00:16:19,649 --> 00:16:22,110
And he's like, when I'm back in the US, I'll trade.

461
00:16:22,110 --> 00:16:23,409
Right now I'm taking it easy.

462
00:16:23,409 --> 00:16:25,950
And it was such a good lesson and it still sticks with me.

463
00:16:25,950 --> 00:16:28,190
So understand if the market is slow

464
00:16:28,190 --> 00:16:30,769
or if you just wanna relax, that's okay too.

465
00:16:30,769 --> 00:16:32,250
The market will always be there.

466
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:35,049
So learn from history, learn from seasonality,

467
00:16:35,049 --> 00:16:37,129
learn from what works best for you too.

468
00:16:37,129 --> 00:16:38,429
Some people will say, Tim,

469
00:16:38,429 --> 00:16:39,830
shouldn't you just trade all the time?

470
00:16:39,830 --> 00:16:41,049
There's so much money to be made.

471
00:16:41,049 --> 00:16:43,330
Yes, but it is also mentally draining.

472
00:16:43,330 --> 00:16:44,730
It's actually very important.

473
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:46,070
Even if the market is on fire,

474
00:16:46,070 --> 00:16:48,409
sometimes you just need to take a day off, a week off.

475
00:16:48,409 --> 00:16:50,210
I know some traders who take a month off,

476
00:16:50,210 --> 00:16:51,330
even if they're crushing it,

477
00:16:51,330 --> 00:16:53,129
you have to protect your mental health too.

478
00:16:53,129 --> 00:16:55,129
Lesson number 11, be open-minded

479
00:16:55,129 --> 00:16:57,889
to trading all types of assets, okay?

480
00:16:57,889 --> 00:17:00,049
The market has changed, the world has changed,

481
00:17:00,049 --> 00:17:01,009
and we're traders.

482
00:17:01,009 --> 00:17:05,089
So it's okay to trade crypto, NFTs, AI, gold,

483
00:17:05,089 --> 00:17:08,250
anything that can take off and really outperform.

484
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:10,450
You don't just have to focus on the FAANG stocks

485
00:17:10,450 --> 00:17:13,690
or mutual funds and try to beat the S&P 500,

486
00:17:13,690 --> 00:17:17,009
which spikes what allows the eight to 10% per year.

487
00:17:17,009 --> 00:17:20,369
There's so much upside in a lot of these lesser known

488
00:17:20,369 --> 00:17:23,569
niches, as I always say, but if you're open-minded,

489
00:17:23,569 --> 00:17:24,849
you can participate.

490
00:17:24,849 --> 00:17:28,130
And if you want me to make a video on crypto,

491
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:29,329
let me know in the comments,

492
00:17:29,329 --> 00:17:31,970
because I'm honestly not sure how many of you

493
00:17:31,970 --> 00:17:32,970
are interested in this,

494
00:17:32,970 --> 00:17:34,529
but I think it might be useful for you.

495
00:17:34,529 --> 00:17:37,130
Lesson number 12, admit when you're wrong

496
00:17:37,130 --> 00:17:38,809
and cut losses quickly.

497
00:17:38,809 --> 00:17:40,470
If you click below, I have a whole video

498
00:17:40,470 --> 00:17:43,049
where literally I talk about cutting losses quickly,

499
00:17:43,049 --> 00:17:45,009
nonstop, that's the only thing I say.

500
00:17:45,009 --> 00:17:47,289
It's so important, because if an investment,

501
00:17:47,289 --> 00:17:49,289
or let's say a relationship is heading

502
00:17:49,289 --> 00:17:52,369
in the wrong direction, cut it, save yourself time

503
00:17:52,369 --> 00:17:54,410
and grief, life is too short.

504
00:17:54,410 --> 00:17:56,890
It's so, so difficult and draining

505
00:17:56,890 --> 00:18:00,009
to be in a bad relationship or in a bad position.

506
00:18:00,009 --> 00:18:01,170
It's not just about the money.

507
00:18:01,170 --> 00:18:03,210
Remember, you have to protect your mental health.

508
00:18:03,210 --> 00:18:06,829
I'll tell you, my biggest loss was Cygnus E-Transactions.

509
00:18:06,829 --> 00:18:09,549
This was a company I believed in, printed home ticketing.

510
00:18:09,549 --> 00:18:10,950
I was right about the technology.

511
00:18:10,950 --> 00:18:12,329
I was wrong about the company.

512
00:18:12,329 --> 00:18:15,210
They went bankrupt and it took several months

513
00:18:15,210 --> 00:18:16,049
to go bankrupt.

514
00:18:16,049 --> 00:18:18,529
And unfortunately, I didn't know about cut losses

515
00:18:18,529 --> 00:18:19,369
quickly back then.

516
00:18:19,369 --> 00:18:21,190
I didn't know about trading liquid stocks.

517
00:18:21,190 --> 00:18:22,670
I actually had restricted shares,

518
00:18:22,670 --> 00:18:24,029
so I couldn't even sell.

519
00:18:24,029 --> 00:18:26,609
And the stock every day would just go lower and lower

520
00:18:26,609 --> 00:18:28,210
because pretty much everyone knew

521
00:18:28,210 --> 00:18:29,849
that they were heading into bankruptcy.

